node.text:
Are you looking to elevate your leadership skills at work or at home? 🤔

One of the biggest roadblocks I see my coaching clients hit is that their team, their family, their community — they don't have any autonomy in the vision.

As a leader, it's your duty to include others in both the creating and deciding. When people can participate and have a hand in the creating process, they will be more engaged, excited, hardworking, and excellent! Remember — people support what they create!

So how are you performing as a leader? Are you allowing others to have a real contribution and a voice in the process? This is SUCH an important question to ask yourself and reflect on when you're in a leadership role. 👏

Comment below with some leadership techniques you are striving to be better at! 👇

node.text:
People want a voice in the decision-making! 📣 

As a leader, it is your duty to honor that, celebrate that, and intentionally practice that by allowing your team members to participate in those needle-moving conversations. When people feel like they have skin in the game, when they feel like they are actively contributing and a part of the creation, they will support you and your mission. 

You set the standard for what kind of team and communication will transpire. So be that positive example and influence for your team! Allow them a space to feel seen, heard, and appreciated for their ideas. 

That, my friends, is the defining duty and quality that separates a good leader from a GREAT one. 👏

node.text:
You might be getting a lot done, BUT…if you don’t feel aligned, you’re getting the WRONG things done. 

Listen — things are going to feel hard to you if they are not:

▶️ in alignment with your true passions and interests
▶️ bringing up curiosity and enthusiasm
▶️ filling you up when you’re doing it

So if you’re wondering why you just can’t get into something or you’ve lost your motivation, it’s not that something is wrong with you. Maybe something simply isn’t in alignment for you.

Think about it. Does that feel true?

Some #tuesdaythoughts for you, and cheering you on along the way. Your coach,
- Brendon.

"Brendon, you're CRAZY!" Just hear me out, okay? I know SO many couples who have all the love in the world, but without enthusiasm, without vibrancy, without spark, there will always be something missing. 🤭

It's time you really dig deep and take a closer look at your relationship. Are you and your partner *excited* about sharing and building a life together? Do you tackle your problems with real *enthusiasm* for the solution? 

I'm telling y'all, this is the secret ingredient to any successful relationship. I challenge you to lean into this idea. Show up for your partner. Bring aliveness and excitement to your relationship — for better or for worse. When you treat your joy and your conflict with the same enthusiasm, when you share a passion to build your futures together, when you face your problems head-on, THAT is when the magic starts. ❤️

Yep, still at it, day 5111.

Yesterday, I posted how I’d crossed 5110 days of writing or recording for you. That’s 14 years, four quotes, posts or recording. 

I couldn’t believe it when I saw the file number it really hit me. 

Got soooo much gratitude for that post in the comments and makes me smile!! appreciate you all.

Whatever you do or dream of, please remember that belief, joy and CONSISTENCY will deliver for you… every day of the journey not just when  you’ve “made it.”

I just wanted to be a writer, teacher and coach. 

So I did that every day. 
When no one knew me. 
Still today. 

Someone pointed out my first book was actually 2001, which was 20 years ago, not 14 years. So yes I’ve been at it for 20 years. The thing with the 5110 days post is that that’s my CONSECUTIVE tally, not cumulative. 
So, shout-out to all of you who put in the days and nights no one ever counts or sees. 
Keep at it. 
Keep doing the work. 
Believe.

Your coach,
Brendon.

#consistency #passion #motivation #writer #coach #happy #milestone #goals #thebrendonshow

node.text:
You know I don’t do many selfies or public celebrations. But today I saw a count in my creative file that made me smile. 

File #5110. 

Each file is one day, and holds four quotes or pieces of writing I did that day. So…

5110 days = 14 years.

This means every day since 2007 I have written or recorded something for you. 

Thats how long you’ve been in my heart. 

This isn’t about posts for me. 

It’s my life’s work. 

It’s my heart. 

It’s my passion and unique library of art that I hope has ripple effects of goodness in the world.

Thank you for the support all these 5110 days.

In gratitude, your coach Brendon.

Just getting warmed up.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '1 Gratitude Shows Up in Your Calendar Your confidence is in your calendar. Manage your calendar well, and progress comes in. When you're doing things consistently that matter to you, your brain goes, Hey, had this intention of doing it. feel confident.' So today want you to decide to retake your agenda, your life's schedule. @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2 Eliminate the Things that Don't Serve You What are some things you need to immediately stop doing in your life? Is minimizing the amount of useless chit-chat that doesn't add to anything in your life? Is it social media? Is it TV? s just not being organized? What do you need to stop doing to take back control of life? Also, what do you need to start doing? And what do you need to start doing every day, every week, every month, every year, to be on your A-game? @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3 Get Better Mentors and Coaches Having people tell you, "Focus on this, not that," will help make your career progress faster. Ifyou ever started your own business or career, if you wander and you just start doing stuff, it might take three or five years to breakthrough. But if someone said, "Hey, just do this." Boom! You can cut three or five years off the learning curve. @brendonbd'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 Set Monthly Challenges Every first of the month, review what's upcoming in your calendar Think about how to do those things with excellence, and also ask if there's anything you need to cut out? Do you need to change some plans based on the way you rescheduled? But most importantly, every single month, plan out whether or not you're going to achieve your projects. What are your deadlines? What are you working on? @brendonburhard'.
